Classification models

To build a classification model we need to create a custom DataLoader. With the get_classification_dls function we get the training and validation examples (with hard negatives) from the train_multi DataFrame built in the core module.

{% raw %}

get_classification_dls[source]

get_classification_dls(bs, with_tfms:bool=True, size=None)

Dataloaders from train DataFrame

{% endraw %} {% raw %}
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
bs = 4
dls = get_classification_dls(bs)
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
dls.train.show_batch(figsize=(15, 3))
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
dls.valid.show_batch(figsize=(15, 3))
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
x, y = dls.train.one_batch()
x.shape, y.shape

(torch.Size([4, 3, 256, 1600]), torch.Size([4, 5]))
{% endraw %}
